Rating: 4
I made this for Christmas and it was fantastic. Based on the other reviews I really wanted to brine the roast. After reading several different brine recipes, I came up with my own that worked out very well. Here's what I did: I mixed 6 cups each water and apple cider, 3/4 cup kosher salt, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 3 t dried rubbed sage, 3 T ground black pepper, and a head of garlic cloves mashed with a knife and lightly chopped. I warmed this on stove to disolve the salt and brown sugar, then put the roast (about 5 1/2 lbs.) in. I put the covered pot in the fridge for 48 hours. I rinsed and patted the roast dry before proceeding with the recipe. I didn't buy the roast in the crown presentation. I also did the stuffing on the side (about 45 mins in the oven at 350 in a covered dish.) I may have missed out on the presentation, but the taste was fabulous!

